 To save data to localStorage in JavaScript, you can use the `setItem()` method. Here's an example:

```javascript
localStorage.setItem("key", "value");
```

To read back from localStorage, you can use the `getItem()` method. Here's an example:

```javascript
let storedValue = localStorage.getItem("key");
console.log(storedValue); // Outputs: value
```

You can also check if a key exists in localStorage using the `hasItem()` method, like this:

```javascript
if (localStorage.hasItem("key")) {
    console.log("Key exists");
} else {
    console.log("Key does not exist");
}
```

Finally, you can remove an item from localStorage using the `removeItem()` method:

```javascript
localStorage.removeItem("key");
```
